President Biden is set to welcome President Iván Duque Márquez of Colombia to the White House on March 10, 2022. The visit will mark 200 years of positive diplomatic relations between the two countries and will provide an opportunity to discuss various regional and global issues of mutual interest. These include Russia's military invasion of Ukraine, the promotion of democracy, security, and prosperity in the hemisphere. The leaders plan to reaffirm the bilateral relationship, discuss COVID-19 response and future pandemic preparedness, economic recovery, and regional responses to migration. The meeting aims to deepen the strategic partnership between the United States and Colombia.